Yes, I was told to go ahead and put it in core when asking about it here #10761 but I can move it to contrib if we need to do that.

So one of the errors I see is the api compatibility test failure which I thought would be fixed by running

    $ bazel build tensorflow/tools/api/tests:api_compatibility_test
    $ bazel-bin/tensorflow/tools/api/tests/api_compatibility_test \
          --update_goldens True

but it still seems to be showing up.

There also seems to be some other issues that came up on the Windows Cmake Tests that I need to address. I might not be able to work on it until next weekend.

Let me know if you still want me to move it to contrib after all.

body:
Yes, I was told to go ahead and put it in core when asking about it here #10761 but I can move it to contrib if we need to do that. 

So one of the errors I see is the api compatibility test failure which I thought would be fixed by running
```
    $ bazel build tensorflow/tools/api/tests:api_compatibility_test
    $ bazel-bin/tensorflow/tools/api/tests/api_compatibility_test \
          --update_goldens True
```
but it still seems to be showing up.

There also seems to be some other issues that came up on the Windows Cmake Tests that I need to address. I might not be able to work on it until next weekend.

Let me know if you still want me to move it to contrib after all.
